<TEXT>
surfing long associated with 
gidget the beach boys and emptyheaded frivolity is being used by 
some young christians to spread the gospel 
we like to call it surfing for jesus said james gould a 
youth counselor at a christian ministry in fort lauderdale im 
sure the lord approves 
the calvary chapel surfing association now with about 70 
members throughout south florida intends to incorporate christian 
teachings into the youth culture of surfing gould said 
theres still a drug problem with some of our kids said 
gould but mostly we have just good christian kids who happen to 
surf surfing has always had a bad rap 
for the past year the group has met once a month on a beach for 
bible readings and prayer a sign says they are ambassadors of 
christ 
the final prayer said gould is for a good set of waves and 
protection from sharks 
i dont think its gods will that anyone be attacked by a 
shark but if it is then it is said gould 33 who has been 
surfing seriously for about three years god created the beach 
the waves and the sky theres a special spiritual feeling being out 
there waiting for a wave 
in goulds small office at the chapel a mile from the beach 
crosses and religious symbols hang next to photographs and surfing 
trinkets such as a figurine of garfield the cartoon cat riding a 
wave 
one of goulds boards has the decal jesus team usa 
you just have to say we are christs ambassadors to the 
surfing scene said gould 
rob craft 17 said the surfing is what got me into all this 
i never thought of mixing church and surfing but you can really do 
it 
but there are some who do not make the connection 
willie smith said an airbrush painter balked at writing jesus 
rules on smiths board andre letast said others just turn a deaf 
ear 
sometime they say get away from me i dont want to hear that 
jesus stuff he said but i think deeply of him hes always 
with me and i want other people to know he can be with them too 
the idea of surfing for jesus began in the mid1980s in a calvary 
chapel church in costa mesa calif which has taped telephone 
messages to tell members about the next surfing contests 
up the coast in ventura calif professional surfer chris burke 
is organizing christian surf retreats for youths in mazatlan 
mexico the first camp this year had 50 participants and the next 
four are sold out said burke next september surfers for missions 
international is planning a retreat in tahiti 
when i was growing up surfing there was nothing like this you 
know it was the laidback laissezfaire attitude said burke 
24 a member of the us amateur team from 1984 to 1986 it just 
sort of hit me that i could use surfing as a way to evangelize 
gould said he believes if jesus were a late20th century figure 
he would be a surfer or a rock musician and take part in other 
youthoriented activities to help teens with problems of drugs and 
alienation 
jesus would probably not even use a board said gould hed 
probably get out there and ride the waves in his bare feet 
