rivalries between hispanics and other americans have 
crowded out issues in the tight emotioncharged race for the us 
house seat left vacant by the death of democratic rep claude pepper 
voting tuesday is expected to be by ethnic more than party 
lines with hispanics rallying around a havanaborn woman trying to 
become the first cubanamerican in congress and most nonlatin 
whites and blacks turning out for a brooklynborn jewish attorney 
that scenario indicated in polling would result in a photofinish 
race 
while pepper a national advocate for the elderly and poor who 
died may 30 at age 88 overwhelmed opponents for 27 years and drew 
no opposition last year tuesdays special election is the 
culmination of one of the most bitter campaigns florida has seen 
attorney gerald richman making his first run for elective 
office defied political pundits and his own partys local hierarchy 
