<TEXT>
christopher w french who during his 23 
years with the associated press was a newsman administrator and 
editor of the ap stylebook has died he was 49 
frenchs wife sarah discovered his body at their home in this 
new york city suburb friday after returning from a visit to 
relatives out of state the cause of death was not immediately 
determined 
since 1980 french was editor of the ap stylebook a 284page 
manual that prescribes word usage punctuation and other guidelines 
for news writing and is used by news media across the nation 
the bostonborn journalist was a political science graduate of 
the university of north carolina at chapel hill where he studied 
under a navy scholarship after four years of navy service 
including stints as a gunnery personnel and public relations 
officer he joined the ap in 1966 as a newsman in the news services 
chattanooga tenn office 
in 1969 he was assigned to nashville the main tennessee bureau 
in 197172 he was a political reporter at the tennessee statehouse 
and helped cover the 1972 national presidential campaign including 
the national party conventions in november 1972 he was named state 
editor in tennessee 
french transferred in 1974 to the general desk in new york the 
central ap news desk where he was a national editor and supervisor 
six years later he was appointed ap stylebook editor in that 
position which he has recently shared as coeditor he updated the 
manual annually to include new subject areas and take account of 
changing times and usages 
among other editorial responsibilities at the general desk 
french was editor of the ap industry news advisory a compilation of 
reports on developments within the news industry that is transmitted 
weekly on ap wires 
since 1981 he also held the position of general desk 
administrative assistant for technology he acted as liaison between 
the editorial and technical staffs and helped introduce new 
computer systems into the ap headquarters in new york 
besides his wife the former sarah quackenboss he is survived by 
two daughters emily and catherine by a sister suzanne french 
obrien of hopkinton nh and by his mother thelma westerling 
french of massachusetts 
a memorial service will be conducted at 2 pm tuesday at christ 
episcopal church in east norwalk in lieu of flowers the family 
asked that contributions be made to the donors charity of choice 
</TEXT>
