<TEXT>
a group founded to promote baby crib safety 
said it is asking the consumer product safety commission today to 
recall millions of cribs because protruding corner posts can snag a 
childs clothing and cause strangulation 
the danny foundation named for a california boy who became 
braindamaged after his shirt got caught on a crib post is seeking 
a ban on protruding corner posts or knobs on cribs 
it is time for the government and crib manufacturers to 
acknowledge these dangerous cribs and prevent further deaths and 
injuries said jack walsh executive director of the foundation 
nearly 50 children have died and two have been left permanently 
brain damaged since 1973 as a result of getting caught on crib 
posts the foundations petition said 
the current voluntary safety standard for cribs adopted in 1984 
which allows corner posts to protrude fiveeighths of an inch 
doesnt protect against strangulation because that is still long 
enough to catch an infants clothing necklace or pacifier cord the 
foundation said in a statement it said a recent study of children 
climbing out of cribs found that two became caught on cornerposts 
that complied with the standard 
believe it or not when this standard was adopted consumers in 
the group opted for the fiveeighthsinch standard because it 
allowed for a less expensive crib almost 16 at the retail level 
on a price of 110 for a crib aaron locker general counsel of 
the juvenile products manufacturers association said today on abcs 
good morning america 
but walsh said it is clear that the voluntary standard is 
inadequate cribs that comply with the curent standard are as 
hazardous as the millions of cribs manufactured before the 
standard 
the foundation in addition to urging a recall of unsafe 
cribs and a ban on protruding cornerposts asked the safety 
commission to mount an information campaign to warn consumers of the 
dangers of the cribs 
there are up to 25 million handmedown cribs in this country 
alone which continue to present a danger walsh said 
the danny foundation a nonprofit organization dedicated to 
promoting crib safety was founded by the family of danny 
lineweaver a child who became severely brain damaged in july 1984 
just short of his second birthday when his shirt got caught on a 
post as he was climbing out of his crib the child remains comatose 
