<TEXT>
irans militia allies held funerals monday 
for the victims of the deadliest israeli raid of 1989 and buried 
them in the shiite moslem country of south lebanon 
hezbollah or party of god said nine people were killed and 27 
wounded in the sixminute air strike sunday on a hezbollah base in 
ain abusuar village it identified the dead as three guerrillas and 
six civilians and claimed 15 children were wounded by a rocket that 
hit a school 
police confirmed the hezbollah figures but said all nine dead 
were guerrillas they said the school building had been abandoned 
long ago and hezbollah used it as an ammunition dump 
in beirut the foreign ministry said it had instructed lebanons 
acting delegate to the united nations shawki shweiri to complain 
about the raid to the security council 
the death toll at ain abusuar was the highest of israels nine 
air raids in lebanon this year by police count eight people were 
killed and 67 wounded in the eight previous raids 
israeli jets broke the sound barrier in reconnaissance flights 
monday over the bekaa valley of east lebanon drawing antiaircraft 
fire from hezbollah positions in janta village and the ancient city 
of baalbek 
beirut radio stations mistook the sonic booms for bomb 
explosions but police hezbollah and the israeli military said the 
planes did not attack 
five bodies from the sunday raid were taken from hospital morgues 
in beirut and sent to south lebanon in a convoy of seven buses 20 
cars and two ambulances for burial in their hometowns 
hezbollah militiamen escorting the flagbedecked motorcade fired 
in the air in a traditional lebanese expression of mourning in 
sidon the convoy divided taking two victims to the southern port 
of tyre and three to nabatiyeh an inland market town 
about 100 mourners buried the other four in the ain abusuar 
cemetery clenching their fists and chanting death to israel 
and death to america armed militiamen prevented photographers 
from taking pictures and reporters were kept at a distance of 200 
yards 
its a security precaution for your own safety a hezbollah 
guerrilla said the israelis might be tempted to strike again if 
there is a big gathering 
ain abusuar is on the northern edge of israels security 
zone in south lebanon a border area 6 to 10 miles deep patrolled 
jointly by israeli soldiers and a predominantly christian surrogate 
militia called the south lebanon army 
sundays raid was an apparent response to a suicide truck bomb 
attack in the zone aug 9 that wounded five israeli soldiers and an 
allied militiaman 
hezbollah said the suicide bombing was vengeance for the israeli 
kidnapping july 28 of sheik abdulkarim obeid a shiite cleric 
associated with the group 
israel has offered to trade him for three captured israel 
soldiers and the 16 western hostages in lebanon who include eight 
americans hezbollah is believed to sponsor shiite groups that hold 
most of the hostages 
</TEXT>
