a court monday rejected the appeal 
of an underground publisher who was sentenced to 2 years in prison 
following his conviction on incitement charges the state news 
agency said 
frantisek starek was convicted of manufacturing and duplicating 
written documents hostile to the socialist state the news agency 
ctk said the maximum sentence he could have received is five years 
in jail 
the court also rejected the appeal for stareks fiancee iva 
vojtkova who received two years probation after being convicted of 
complicity ctk said 
the june 28 conviction of starek was one of a series of trials 
this year in a crackdown on dissent in czechoslovakia 
starek 36 has spent 38 months in jail in the past 13 years and 
undergone repeated police harassment for his involvement in 
independent culture 
he was arrested on feb 23 on the incitement charge police 
searched his home and confiscated his typewriter his computer and 
printer and a complete unpublished issue of vokno his 
