a decent pair of shoes is as hard to find 
as a patch of flat land in this coal mining community now that the 
last clothing store has shut its doors 
the strike against the pittston coal group is slowly suffocating 
dickenson county where nearly a third of the striking united mine 
workers live 
the county had been in an economic downturn for more than four 
years when the strike began april 5 since then the county has lost 
coal tax revenue the school budget has been cut deeply and 
businesses have been hurt by the lack of buying power 
the countys unemployment rate for july announced monday was 
