<TEXT>
a prosecutor said in court monday that former 
officials of the mexican government may be implicated in connection 
with the torture murder of us drug agent enrique camarena 
the comments by assistant us attorney jimmy gurule came during 
a federal hearing at which he won the continued imprisonment of a 
material witness who is the brotherinlaw of former mexican 
president luis echeverria 
the prosecutor told us district judge edward rafeedie that the 
political clout of ruben zuno arce makes him a key witness in 
the ongoing probe of camarenas 1985 murder 
gurule said the government now believes that corrupt political 
officials and law enforcement officers at higher levels were 
present at a guadalajara home during a brutal interrogation of 
camarena in the hours before he was murdered 
gurules courtroom comments were made to support continued 
imprisonment of zuno who has been held since aug 9 as a material 
witness without any charges filed against him 
zuno testified before a grand jury last thursday but gurule said 
he did not conclude the questioning and wants him to return next 
thursday 
rafeedie asked for a general indication of the testimony in order 
to decide whether to keep the witness in prison 
there were denials regarding his association with narcotics 
traffickers said gurule but there were admissions of his 
association with political officials at the highest level 
including president lopez portillo he could place calls 
and the president of mexico would answer immediately he had that 
type of political clout 
gurule said he believes that zuno acted as a gobetween for 
politicians and drug traffickers including rafael caro quintero 
caro has been accused of ordering camarenas execution and is 
awaiting trial in mexico 
camarena allegedly was tortured and murdered at a home that caro 
bought indirectly from zuno gurule said the government wants 
information about transfer of the property 
the kidnapping and torture murder of camarena and his pilot 
alfredo zavalaavelar became an international incident the drug 
enforcement administration has vowed to bring in every person 
involved in the murders several members of the mexican federal 
police force were linked to the killings and one raul lopez 
alvarez was convicted last year along with two drug traffickers 
camarena and zavala were killed after the narcotics agent led a 
series of damaging raids on marijuana plantations allegedly operated 
by caro authorities have said 
camarenas body was found march 5 1985 on a ranch 65 miles 
southeast of guadalajara 
seven more men are charged with murder and conspiracy in the 
case including caro this month a grand jury indicted yet another 
defendant former mexican police officer juan jose bernabe ramirez 
his trial is set for oct 3 and the government wants zuno to testify 
against him 
zunos lawyers argued futilely for his immediate release saying 
he has been roughed up while in custody and is being denied 
visits with his wife who is echeverrias sister 
i dont think they could do this with an american citizen 
said attorney edward medvene just because hes mexican its not 
fair 
rafeedie who ordered prison officials to allow visits by zunos 
wife ordered zunos continued imprisonment while he concludes his 
testimony before the grand jury after that the judge said he 
wants lawyers to file briefs on why the witness cannot be released 
the judge scheduled a hearing for sept 5 to consider zunos 
future status 
outside court gurule declined to comment on when further 
indictments might be expected in the camarena case saying only 
we are hopeful there will be more to come 
