arabamericans have been part of the fabric of 
american society for more than 100 years but the current wave of 
immigrants fleeing the destruction and death in their homelands 
has reawakened their ethnic sense and brought problems in 
microcosm here is a look this slice of america today 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
an arabamerican community center is burned 
twice a couple returns home from their mosque to find go back 
scrawled in shoe polish on their walls and carpet 
they put sludge in my pita bread took my lunchmeat out they 
