for delivery in september at 7302 cents a pound feeder cattle were 
30 cent to 103 cents lower with august at 8337 cents a pound 
the decline extended a twoweekold trend that analysts 
attributed largely to consumers reduced appetite for heavy beef 
products during the hottest part of the summer 
people dont fix many pot roasts in august they dont want to 
heat up the house said thomas morgan president of sterling 
research corp of arlington heights ill 
gordon linn president of chicagobased linnco futures inc said 
the cattle markets typically slow late in august after retailers 
have completed their buying of beef destined for labor day weekend 
cookouts 
