<TEXT>
general motors corp announced plans 
monday to lay off 600 assembly line workers in november at its 
arlington plant and to idle the plant for two weeks beforehand a 
union official said 
plant managers told crews about the layoffs and the 
administration met with union representatives about the plans said 
buddy stewart president of united automobile workers local 276 
he said the plant will close for oneweek periods on sept 24 and 
oct 30 after that about 600 workers wont return when production 
resumes the week of nov 6 
the plant builds gms largest rearwheeldrive cars the 
chevrolet caprice and the cadillac brougham it also produces 
chevrolet buick and oldsmobile station wagons 
gm officials could not be reached for comment monday by the 
associated press 
